node.text:
Meet Neron the Black Jaguar - He has most incredible markings you’ll ever see on a feline! 🤩🐈‍⬛

📸 by @thebigcatsanctuaryuk

Jaguars are the largest felines in the Americas. Adult males can reach an overall length of more than 7 feet, and can weigh anywhere from 150 to 200 pounds. 

Their coats color and markings are very similar to the leopard, with a rich tawny or yellow background with large black rosettes and spots. They have larger heads, more compact bodies, and much more powerful paws! 

The Jaguar also occurs with an all black (melanistic) coat, and like the leopard, the spots can still be seen on black individuals. Albino individuals have been reported as well.

node.text:
🐍 Atheris is a genus of venomous vipers known as bush vipers. They are found only in tropical sub-Saharan Africa (excluding southern Africa) and many species have isolated and fragmented distributions due to their confinement to rain forests. In an example of convergent evolution, they show many similarities to the arboreal pit vipers of Asia and South America. Seventeen species are currently recognized.

This one in the video is called Atheris chlorechis / Western bush viper. Make sure not to miss the cute eye move at the very end.

_____

🐁🦎🐸 Atheris species have been known to prey upon a variety of small amphibians, lizards, rodents, birds, and even other snakes. Some species or populations favor eating frogs, but most have been described as opportunistic feeders. Prey is typically ambushed from a hanging position, held until it has succumbed to the venom and then swallowed.
Not much is known about their venom except that it is strongly hemotoxic, causing pain, swelling and blood clotting problems. Until recently, their venom has often been regarded as less toxic than that of many other species, perhaps because bites are uncommon, but this turned out not to be the case. There are now a number of reports of bites that have led to severe hemorrhaging. One case was fatal. Atheris-specific antivenom does not exist and antivenom meant for bites from other species seem to have little effect, although Echis antivenom has been reported to have been of some help in a case of A. squamigera envenomation.

_____
